eact upon one another.', 32, 0), (496632, 'At the heart of these challenges lies the question of how the institutions of the European Union make laws, the types of laws they pass and the effectiveness with which those laws are implemented on civil society and the economy.', 66758, 0), (496633, 'It is, I believe, the greatest generation any society has ever produced.', 11429, 0), (496634, 'The winner of the hoop race will be the first to realize her dream, not society''s dream, her own personal dream.', 11962, 0), (496635, 'The endurance of the inequalities of life by the poor is the marvel of human society.', 20855, 0), (496636, 'Justice must always question itself, just as society can exist only by means of the work it does on itself and on its institutions.', 833, 0), (496637, 'So is civil society prepared for the future? Probably not. Most organisations have to live hand to mouth, juggling short-term funding and perpetual minor crises. Even the bigger ones rarely get much time to stand back and look at the bigger picture. Many are on a treadmill chasing after contracts and new funding.', 70907, 0), (496638, 'It is our responsibility to explain to the public how an often unpredictable system of justice is one that serves a productive, civilized, but always evolving, society.', 11622, 0), (496639, 'The love of the family, the love of one person can heal. It heals the scars left by a larger society. A massive, powerful society.', 74, 0), (496640, 'Infant mortality and life expectancy are reasonable indicators of general well-being in a society.', 10731, 0), (496641, 'Exclusiveness in a garden is a mistake as great as it is in society.', 19352, 0), (496642, 'The world is governed more by appearance than realities so that it is fully as necessary to seem to know something as to know it.', 3308, 0), (496643, 'Cockroaches and socialites are the only things that can stay up all night and eat anything.', 59745, 0), (496644, 'It is incontestable and deplorable that Negroes