re a kid who is always on the outside hoping to be on the inside, you''re watching a lot. You''re trying to figure out how to become a normal person in a society that considers you weird.', 1618, 0), (496822, 'We live in a multi-cultural society far more open to international ideas. If you''d told me 20 years ago I''d drive through Bury and see someone sitting outside a cafe drinking a latte, I''d have laughed. In fact, I wouldn''t have even known what a latte was.', 71260, 0), (496823, 'We are shifting from a managerial society to an entrepreneurial society.', 62795, 0), (496824, 'The key to organizing an alternative society is to organize people around what they can do, and more importantly, what they want to do.', 10121, 0), (496825, 'I like to describe myself as a proudly visible member of the most invisible segments of our society - older women.', 75994, 0), (496826, 'At a time when India is going through great changes and, with China, is likely to inherit the world from the West, it is important that writers like me try to highlight the brutal injustices of society.', 1285, 0), (496827, 'If we were in India now, there would be servants standing in the corners of this room and I wouldn''t notice them. That is what my society is like, that is what the divide is like.', 1285, 0), (496828, 'Persian social manners are well known, and there is no other society that can compete with them.', 76160, 0), (496829, 'I want to be fighting for a society accountable towards its citizens.', 29456, 0), (496830, 'A theme in a lot of my books - and in my own life - is making choices that you feel you should make, or what society wants you to make, as opposed to what is truly right for you.', 303, 0), (496831, 'The first sign of corruption in a society that is still alive is that the end justifies the means.', 4300, 0), (496832, 'The chief product of an automated society is a widespread and deepening sense of boredom.', 61019, 0), (496833, 'However, please allow me to say that the fundamental style of my writing has been to start from my personal matters and then to link it up with society, the state and the world.', 7778, 0), (496834, 'In practice, socialism didn''t work. But socialism could never have worked because it is based on false premises about human psychology and society, and gross ignorance of human economy.', 71537, 0), (496835, 'The judge said I was a menace to society because I had put crime on a scientific basis.', 22363, 0), (496836, 'A society deadened by a smothering network of laws while finding release in moral chaos is not likely to be either happy or stable.', 70805, 0), (496837, 'In polite society one laughs at all the jokes, including the ones one has heard before.', 75464, 0), (496838, 'The priests are debarred from female society, nor is any woman permitted to enter the religious houses.', 68683, 0), (496839, 'My life has been that of someone who has moved from the countryside to the society. To make that transition, I have had to learn a lot.', 67260, 0), (496840, 'I think this society suffers so much from too much freedom, too many rights that allow people to be irresponsible.', 42979, 0), (496841, 'Do not ghettoize society by putting people into legal categories of gender, race, ethnicity, language, or other such characteristics.', 76123, 0), (496842, 'The question I asked Georges has now become a general one - You, who thought you were superfluous, who thought there was no place for you in society, not only are you not superfluous, you are needed and so those who were beggars become givers.', 72334, 0), (496843, 'For centuries we have been living in the society where not laws but people ruled, where there was no legal state.', 68820, 0), (496844, 'Interethnic and spiritual accord is our strategic resource, the basis for progress of our society and state.', 68820, 0), (496845, 'I feel that I''ll be buried in Ireland and don''t think I''ll ever live in the U.S. I''m not comfortable with many aspects of U.S. society - especially the justice system.', 1786, 0), (496846, 'The remedy for speech that is false is speech that is true. This is the ordinary course in a free society. The response to the unreasoned is the rational; to the uninformed, the enlightened; to the straight-out lie, the simple truth.', 66788, 0), (496847, 'To give up the task of reforming society is to give up one''s responsibility as a free man.', 476, 0), (496848, 'The public school has become the established church of secular society.', 11411, 0), (496849, 'What can you say about a society that says that God is dead and Elvis is alive?', 63449, 0), (496850, 'It is good for society to have this introspection.', 76161, 0);
