ething that says, ''You can never become a citizen.'' That''s un-American.', 74629, 0), (497541, 'The president, just as any other American, deserves a legal defense against personal lawsuits not related to his office. But the costs of that defense should be borne by him and not the taxpayer.', 76243, 0), (497542, 'None of the constitutional, legal or other principles bars me from returning to the judiciary, since the judiciary remains independent if the actors remain independent and fair.', 76244, 0), (497543, 'The legal right of a taxpayer to decrease the amount of what otherwise would be his taxes, or altogether avoid them, by means which the law permits, cannot be doubted.', 76245, 0), (497544, 'We got a little waylaid along the way. The whole problem started about 10 years ago with management and legal battles, then still trying to make albums while I was doing all of that.', 76246, 0), (497545, 'The work is challenging, interesting and an important part of our legal system.', 76247, 0), (497546, 'I used to brag that I can hold up any eviction - even if the landlord had legal rights, I could hold it up for a year.', 76248, 0), (497547, 'Does the imam have a legal right to build the mosque at Ground Zero? The answer is yes. But is it the right thing to do? The answer is no. And most Americans, and most moderate Muslims, join with me in that call.', 76249, 0), (497548, 'We believe the use of force against Iraq, especially with reference to previous resolutions of the UN Security Council, has no grounds, including legal grounds.', 76250, 0), (497549, 'By the fulfillment of my legal and moral duty I think I have earned punishment just as little as the tens of thousands of dutiful German officials who have now been imprisoned only because they carried out their duties.', 76251, 0), (497550, 'The Chinese have always enjoyed gambling, and Macau is the only place in Greater China where gambling is legal. So I believe the government understands that there has to be a place for it.', 76252, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (497551, 'From your confessor, lawyer and physician, hide not your case on no condition.', 62676, 0), (497552, 'The job of the Attorney General is very specific. My roll, as the legal adviser, is to defend the constitutionality of the laws as they''re passed.', 76253, 0), (497553, 'I actually don''t have a view on whether someone watching certain material that may be legal in some places, but might be obscene to somebody else, can trigger a violent streak in someone.', 76254, 0), (497554, 'I did this within a philosophical framework, and a moral and legal framework. And I have been turned into a cartoon of the greatest villain in the history of lobbying.', 76255, 0), (497555, 'Well, I think the great tragedy in American politics is what is legal, not what is illegal.', 76255, 0), (497556, 'They can''t collect legal taxes from illegal money.', 13068, 0), (497557, 'A wedding dress is both an intimate and personal for a woman - it must reflect the personality and style of the bride.', 71247, 0), (497558, 'I want to be a simple bride when I get married. I want a beach wedding where I am running around on the sand in a white dress.', 67101, 0), (497559, 'I only wear two rings: a wedding ring and my World Series ring.', 59473, 0), (497560, 'In Hollywood, brides keep the bouquets and throw away the groom.', 1040, 0), (497561, 'My favourite flowers are English country roses - I had a bouquet of them for my wedding.', 12807, 0), (497562, 'People''s hands fascinate me. It''s tempting to look at a businessman''s left hand and see if there''s an indentation from a missing wedding ring. Or maybe there''s a tan line and the skin is pressed down where''s he''s worked a ring off his finger.', 7847, 0), (497563, 'A young bride is like a plucked flower but a guilty wife is like a flower that had been walked over. ', 143, 0), (497564, 'I''d imagine my wedding as a fairy tale... huge, beautiful and white.', 50391, 0), (497565, '