r my cup of tea.', 67484, 0), (497594, 'Even if you believe a creator god invented the laws of physics, would you so insult him as to suggest that he might capriciously and arbitrarily violate them in order to walk on water, or turn water into wine as a cheap party trick at a wedding?', 1716, 0), (497595, 'About 80 percent of the photos on Flickr are public and searchable by everyone. In one sense, it''s a place where people upload snapshots from the family reunion, wedding or the birth of a baby or something like that, but it''s also a place where people go to show what the world looks like to them.', 69523, 0), (497596, 'My wedding was a very private affair for close family and friends, so I had decided to hold a reception in my native town.', 67868, 0), (497597, 'I''ve been looking at some video clips on YouTube of President Obama - then candidate Obama - going through Iowa making promises. The gap between his promises and his performance is the largest I''ve seen, well, since the Kardashian wedding and the promise of ''til death do we part.', 52321, 0), (497598, 'Even if it''s your wedding, if you''re a guy, it''s boring.', 69334, 0), (497599, 'I hated the royal wedding.', 1259, 0), (497600, 'I want a big church wedding.', 67853, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (497601, 'There is no way in the world anyone else could do my wedding other than myself, along with whomever I select to do various things.', 67725, 0), (497602, 'I don''t really have many regrets. I did miss a lot of the events in the days leading up to my sister''s wedding because I was at a U17 camp. There were moments like that growing up when I felt like I focused too much on soccer. But that''s probably the reason I am where I am today.', 67841, 0), (497603, 'Most kids don''t get to go their parents'' wedding.', 71236, 0), (497604, 'I love a black wedding dress.', 66693, 0), (497605, 'Valentino made my day suit for the wedding of Paloma Picasso in Paris.', 72369, 0), (497606, 'If you''re going to plan a wedding, then a certain amount of suffering is not a choice.', 71045, 0), (497607, 'You can have a wedding at Fenway Park.', 71051, 0), (497608, 'If you''re engaged more than a year, there''s something up. There''s lot of debate as to whether one should or shouldn''t get married, but when you get engaged, it''s a promise to get married, and if you don''t just do it within a year, one of the parties is using the excuse of, like, ''I can''t find the right venue'' to put off the wedding.', 47435, 0), (497609, 'I can see why people love the idea of a big white wedding - it is a day when they are the centre of attention and get to wear a beautiful dress. But that sounds awful to me because that is like getting ready to walk down the red carpet.', 74434, 0), (497610, 'The one thing that I''m in charge of in this wedding is the food.', 76257, 0), (497611, 'I had a huge Indian wedding, and I did it for my wife, and I did it for my white friends.', 68420, 0), (497612, 'I love 3-D. I have been a big fan of 3-D for a long, long time. I took my 1988 wedding pictures in 3-D!', 68139, 0), (497613, 'O month when they who love must love and wed.', 25904, 0), (497614, 'I think a lot of people get so obsessed with the wedding and the expense of the wedding that they miss out on what the real purpose is. It''s not about a production number, it''s about a meaningful moment between two people that''s witnessed by people that they actually really know and care about.', 64133, 0), (497615, 'Our whole wedding cost 180 bucks. Afterward, we re-heated lasagna for everyone and set off fireworks.', 70237, 0), (497616, 'I did get to keep the wedding dresses from ''Runaway Bride''. They''re all boxed up in my garage. I''ve never opened them. It''ll be fun one day when Hazel is taller. She can play dress-up with her friends.', 64247, 0), (497617, 'What the bride should do is call guests who have young children and say: ''I''d love to have the kids at the wedding, but we won''t have room. Would you get a baby sitter, and when we get back from our honeymoon, we''ll have you guys over?''', 70057, 0), (497618, 'I do not have a bride gene. I haven''t been planning a wedding since I was 3. I never put a sheet on my head and pretended that it was a veil.', 68970, 0), (497619, 'As a child, as a cinemagoer, I think there is nothing better than being in a cinema or watching a film. I think it''s just a while magical... it almost feels like you''re at a big party in India, where you''re singing, you''re dancing, you''re laughing, you''re crying, you feel like you''re at a wedding because our films invariably cover all emotions.', 67066, 0), (497620, 'The chain of wedlock is so heavy that it takes two to carry it - and sometimes three.', 1083, 0), (497621, 'I don''t ever really feel that wearing my wedding ring is what determines me being married or not.', 52064, 0), (497622, 'Recently, I was preparing to sing Springsteen''s ''If I Should Fall Behind'' for a wedding and was unable to get through it without tears. My wife handed me ''Love You Forever.'' I read it. I cried. But that cry somehow cured me of crying while singing the song. Go figure.', 69169, 0), (497623, 'I still love touring rock clubs around 